If users need to compare items,
Similarity causes confusion. Elements that are perceived as similar will likely be confused with one
another. Think of similarity as the ratio of similar features to different features.
This is called redundancy gain. Displays are more likely to be interpreted correctly if the user can rely on
multiple cues for the information. This is especially true when conditions for display interpretation are not
favorable, as in noisy hospital environments.
